# wrappedValue

**Instance Property**

The current value of the environment property.

## Declaration

```swift
var wrappedValue: Value { get }
```

## Discussion

The wrapped value property provides primary access to the value’s data. However, you don’t access `wrappedValue` directly. Instead, you read the property variable created with the [doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Environment] property wrapper:

```swift
@Environment(\.colorScheme) var colorScheme: ColorScheme

var body: some View {
    if colorScheme == .dark {
        DarkContent()
    } else {
        LightContent()
    }
}
```
